   "source": [
    "# PyPopART Basic Workflow\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the basic workflow for constructing and visualizing haplotype networks using PyPopART.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Steps Covered:\n",
    "1. Loading sequence data\n",
    "2. Calculating genetic distances\n",
    "3. Identifying unique haplotypes\n",
    "4. Constructing a haplotype network\n",
    "5. Analyzing network statistics\n",
    "6. Visualizing the network"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import required modules\n",
    "from pypopart.io import load_alignment\n",
    "from pypopart.core.distance import DistanceCalculator\n",
    "from pypopart.core.condensation import condense_alignment\n",
    "from pypopart.algorithms import MJNAlgorithm\n",
    "from pypopart.stats import calculate_network_metrics, calculate_diversity_metrics\n",
    "from pypopart.visualization import StaticNetworkPlotter, InteractiveNetworkPlotter"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Sequence Alignment\n",
    "\n",
    "PyPopART supports multiple sequence file formats including FASTA, NEXUS, PHYLIP, and GenBank."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load alignment from file\n",
    "alignment = load_alignment('../../data/examples/sample.fasta')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(alignment)} sequences\")\n",
    "print(f\"Alignment length: {alignment.length} bp\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display alignment statistics\n",
    "print(\"\\nAlignment Statistics:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Number of sequences: {len(alignment)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Alignment length: {alignment.length} bp\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Variable sites: {alignment.get_variable_sites()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  GC content: {alignment.gc_content():.2f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Calculate Genetic Distances\n",
    "\n",
    "PyPopART provides several distance metrics:\n",
    "- **Hamming**: Simple count of differences\n",
    "- **Jukes-Cantor (JC)**: Corrects for multiple substitutions\n",
    "- **Kimura 2-parameter (K2P)**: Accounts for transitions vs transversions\n",
    "- **Tamura-Nei**: Most complex model, accounts for GC content and rate variation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate distance matrix using Kimura 2-parameter\n",
    "calculator = DistanceCalculator(method='k2p')\n",
    "dist_matrix = calculator.calculate_matrix(alignment)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Distance matrix shape: {dist_matrix.shape}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 5x5 distances:\")\n",
    "print(dist_matrix[:5, :5])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Construct Haplotype Network\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll use the Median-Joining Network algorithm, which automatically identifies unique haplotypes and infers ancestral nodes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Construct Median-Joining Network\n",
    "# The algorithm will automatically identify unique haplotypes\n",
    "mjn = MJNAlgorithm(epsilon=0)  # epsilon=0 for maximum simplification\n",
    "network = mjn.construct_network(alignment, dist_matrix)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Network constructed:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Nodes: {network.num_nodes}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Edges: {network.num_edges}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Count median vectors (inferred ancestral nodes)\n",
    "n_medians = len([n for n in network.graph.nodes() if network.graph.nodes[n].get('is_median', False)])\n",
    "print(f\"  Median vectors (inferred ancestors): {n_medians}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Analyze Network Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "Calculate various network metrics to understand the structure and diversity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate network metrics\n",
    "metrics = calculate_network_metrics(network)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Network Statistics:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Nodes: {network.num_nodes}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Edges: {network.num_edges}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Diameter: {metrics.diameter}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Average path length: {metrics.average_path_length:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Clustering coefficient: {metrics.clustering_coefficient:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Reticulation index: {metrics.reticulation_index:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Connected components: {metrics.num_components}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Visualize the Network\n",
    "\n",
    "### Static Visualization (Matplotlib)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create static visualization\n",
    "plotter = StaticNetworkPlotter(network)\n",
    "fig, ax = plotter.plot(\n",
    "    layout_algorithm='spring',\n",
    "    figsize=(10, 8),\n",
    "    show_labels=True,\n",
    "    title='Haplotype Network (Median-Joining)'\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.savefig('network_static.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print(\"Static plot saved to network_static.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
